{
  "page": "Wedding of Hizdahr zo Loraq and Daenerys Targaryen",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>wedding of Hizdahr zo Loraq and Daenerys Targaryen</b> takes place in <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/300_AC\" title=\"300 AC\">300&#160;AC</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> chooses to marry <a href=\"/index.php/Hizdahr_zo_Loraq\" title=\"Hizdahr zo Loraq\">Hizdahr zo Loraq</a> to help solidify her reign as <a href=\"/index.php/Queen_of_Meereen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Queen of Meereen\">Queen of Meereen</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Prelude\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Prelude</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Wedding\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Wedding</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aftermath\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aftermath</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Attendees\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Attendees</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Prelude\">Prelude</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Hizdahr_zo_Loraq_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Prelude\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> is <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_of_Drogo_and_Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Wedding of Drogo and Daenerys Targaryen\">wed</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Drogo\" title=\"Drogo\">Drogo</a> as part of her brother <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys Targaryen\">Viserys's</a> alliance with the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Khal\" title=\"Khal\">khal</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Drogo later kills Viserys at <a href=\"/index.php/Vaes_Dothrak\" title=\"Vaes Dothrak\">Vaes Dothrak</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> however, and Drogo himself dies from wounds suffered in the <a href=\"/index.php/Dothraki_sea\" title=\"Dothraki sea\">Dothraki sea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot68.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot68.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Daenerys hatches three <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_egg\" title=\"Dragon egg\">dragon eggs</a> place in Drogo's funeral pyre,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot72.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot72.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and she eventually embarks on <a href=\"/index.php/Targaryen_campaign_in_Slaver%27s_Bay\" title=\"Targaryen campaign in Slaver&#39;s Bay\">a campaign</a> to end <a href=\"/index.php/Slavery\" title=\"Slavery\">slavery</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Slaver%27s_Bay\" title=\"Slaver&#39;s Bay\">Slaver's Bay</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Daenerys chooses to rule as <a href=\"/index.php/Queen_of_Meereen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Queen of Meereen\">Queen of Meereen</a> after <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Meereen\" title=\"Siege of Meereen\">conquering the city</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> and the widow refuses marriage offers from <a href=\"/index.php/Cleon_the_Great\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Cleon the Great\">Cleon the Great</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Astapor\" title=\"Astapor\">Astapor</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> and from <a href=\"/index.php/Xaro_Xhoan_Daxos\" title=\"Xaro Xhoan Daxos\">Xaro Xhoan Daxos</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Qarth\" title=\"Qarth\">Qarth</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> Meanwhile, the <a href=\"/index.php/Sons_of_the_Harpy\" title=\"Sons of the Harpy\">Sons of the Harpy</a> resist Daenerys's rule over Meereen by engaging in a <a href=\"/index.php/Shadow_war\" title=\"Shadow war\">shadow war</a> against her supporters.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> To bring peace to the city, <a href=\"/index.php/Galazza_Galare\" title=\"Galazza Galare\">Galazza Galare</a> advises Daenerys to marry a highborn Meereenese man of noble blood, suggesting <a href=\"/index.php/Hizdahr_zo_Loraq\" title=\"Hizdahr zo Loraq\">Hizdahr zo Loraq</a>. Daenerys tells Hizdahr she might be willing to marry him if he can prevent any murders in the city for ninety days and nights.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Barristan_Selmy\" title=\"Barristan Selmy\">Barristan Selmy</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Queensguard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Queensguard\">Lord Commander of the Queensguard</a>, is wary of the idea, telling Daenerys that the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> would never accept Hizdahr as king.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Daario_Naharis\" title=\"Daario Naharis\">Daario Naharis</a> suggests himself as a groom instead but is refused. After the <a href=\"/index.php/Sellsword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellsword\">sellsword</a> suggests that Daenerys massacre the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Masters\" title=\"Great Masters\">Great Masters</a> at the wedding if she marries Hizdahr, the queen decides to send Daario back into the field.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Reznak_mo_Reznak\" title=\"Reznak mo Reznak\">Reznak mo Reznak</a> and Galazza, the <a href=\"/index.php/Green_Grace\" title=\"Green Grace\">Green Grace</a>, discuss wedding preparations and customs with Daenerys. The queen rejects the custom of the bride being examined by the husband's female family members to test for fertility, as well as the custom of the bride washing the groom's feet. Daenerys would prefer to marry using Westerosi rites, but Galazza explains that would be unacceptable to the <a href=\"/index.php/Ghiscari\" title=\"Ghiscari\">Ghiscari</a>. Daenerys learns that the bride is expected to wear dark red veils above a <i><a href=\"/index.php/Tokar\" title=\"Tokar\">tokar</a></i> of white <a href=\"/index.php/Silk\" title=\"Silk\">silk</a> fringed with baby <a href=\"/index.php/Pearl\" title=\"Pearl\">pearls</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> Hizdahr affirms for Daenerys that her enemies, including <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkai</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/New_Ghis\" title=\"New Ghis\">New Ghis</a>, require her to wed as part of any peace treaty to end the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_siege_of_Meereen\" title=\"Second siege of Meereen\">second siege of Meereen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Daenerys sleeps with Daario when he returns to Meereen,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> but continues to refuse his own marriage offers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Quentyn_Martell\" title=\"Quentyn Martell\">Quentyn Martell</a> arrives in Meereen to offer <a href=\"/index.php/Secret_marriage_pact\" title=\"Secret marriage pact\">his own hand in marriage</a> as well, but he is refused by Daenerys as well.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup> The queen commits instead to marrying Hizdahr the next day, though she sleeps with Daario one last time that night.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Wedding\">Wedding</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Hizdahr_zo_Loraq_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Wedding\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marc_Fishman_Dany_wedding.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a3/Marc_Fishman_Dany_wedding.jpg/350px-Marc_Fishman_Dany_wedding.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"293\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a3/Marc_Fishman_Dany_wedding.jpg/525px-Marc_Fishman_Dany_wedding.jpg 1.5x, /images/a/a3/Marc_Fishman_Dany_wedding.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marc_Fishman_Dany_wedding.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a>'s wedding procession, by Marc Fishman ©</div></div></div>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Jhiqui\" title=\"Jhiqui\">Jhiqui</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Irri\" title=\"Irri\">Irri</a> help Daenerys dress in her <i>tokar</i> with pearls. Reznak and <a href=\"/index.php/Skahaz_mo_Kandaq\" title=\"Skahaz mo Kandaq\">Skahaz mo Kandaq</a> request the honor of escorting the queen from the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Pyramid\" title=\"Great Pyramid\">Great Pyramid</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Temple_of_the_Graces\" title=\"Temple of the Graces\">Temple of the Graces</a>. She intends to ride there on her <a href=\"/index.php/Silver_mare\" title=\"Silver mare\">silver mare</a>, but <a href=\"/index.php/Missandei\" title=\"Missandei\">Missandei</a> points out she would be unable to in a <i>tokar</i>. Instead of a <a href=\"/index.php/Palanquin\" title=\"Palanquin\">palanquin</a>, Daenerys agrees to be carried in a sedan chair. Quentyn makes another entreaty, but he is again refused.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>While they travel to the temple, Barristan tells the queen about her parents, King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys II Targaryen\">Aerys II Targaryen</a> and Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaelle_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaelle Targaryen\">Rhaelle Targaryen</a>, and how Rhaelle had once been smitten with a <a href=\"/index.php/Bonifer_Hasty\" title=\"Bonifer Hasty\">young knight</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup> Daenerys's procession is joined by that of Hizdahr, who is being transported in his own sedan chair.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The procession is awaited outside the temple by Galazza and <a href=\"/index.php/Graces\" title=\"Graces\">Graces</a> of various colors. They bring forth an <a href=\"/index.php/Ivory\" title=\"Ivory\">ivory</a> chair with a plush <a href=\"/index.php?title=Velvet&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Velvet (page does not exist)\">velvet</a> seat, as well as a golden bowl so that Hizdahr can wash the queen's feet with warm fragrant oils. Fifty <a href=\"/index.php/Eunuch\" title=\"Eunuch\">eunuchs</a> sing during the public ritual, which is observed by ten thousand eyes. Daenerys and Hizdahr then enter the temple to be wed, and the married couple leaves the building four hours later with their wrist and ankles bound together with chains of yellow <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aftermath\">Aftermath</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Hizdahr_zo_Loraq_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aftermath\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>King Hizdahr decides to reopen the <a href=\"/index.php/Fighting_pits_of_Meereen\" title=\"Fighting pits of Meereen\">fighting pits of Meereen</a> to celebrate the city's peace with Yunkai, and he hosts a feast in the Great Pyramid for the Yunkishmen. Daenerys is displeased that a slave market has been opened by the <a href=\"/index.php/Wise_Masters\" title=\"Wise Masters\">Wise Masters</a> south of the <a href=\"/index.php/Skahazadhan\" title=\"Skahazadhan\">Skahazadhan</a>. Daario is angered by the marriage, so for his own protection Daenerys includes the sellsword among the hostages sent over the Yunkai'i.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Queen Daenerys attends the reopening of <a href=\"/index.php/Daznak%27s_Pit\" title=\"Daznak&#39;s Pit\">Daznak's Pit</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Drogon\" title=\"Drogon\">Drogon</a> appears during the competition, and the queen flies away on his back while attempting to control the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd52.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd52.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> With Daenerys vanished from Meereen, Hizdahr assumes rule over the city.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup> Quentyn attempts to tame one of the dragons confined by the queen to the <a href=\"/index.php/Pit_(Great_Pyramid)\" title=\"Pit (Great Pyramid)\">pit below the Great Pyramid</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd68.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd68.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup> but he is mortally wounded in the attempt and <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaegal\" title=\"Rhaegal\">Rhaegal</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Viserion\" title=\"Viserion\">Viserion</a> are freed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd70.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd70.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Victarion_Greyjoy\" title=\"Victarion Greyjoy\">Victarion Greyjoy</a> sails with the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Fleet\" title=\"Iron Fleet\">Iron Fleet</a> toward Meereen, having been sent by his brother <a href=\"/index.php/Euron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Euron Greyjoy\">Euron</a> to bring Daenerys to Westeros as the Crow's Eye's bride. Victarion intends to marry Daenerys himself, however, and after learning of her marriage he finds himself willing to kill Hizdahr to make Daenerys a widow again.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Attendees\">Attendees</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Hizdahr_zo_Loraq_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Attendees\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\"><img alt=\"Meereen.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/89/Meereen.png/20px-Meereen.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/89/Meereen.png/30px-Meereen.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/89/Meereen.png/40px-Meereen.png 2x\" /></a> King <a href=\"/index.php/Hizdahr_zo_Loraq\" title=\"Hizdahr zo Loraq\">Hizdahr zo Loraq</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\"><img alt=\"Kingsguard.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/20px-Kingsguard.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/30px-Kingsguard.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/40px-Kingsguard.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Barristan_Selmy\" title=\"Barristan Selmy\">Barristan Selmy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\"><img alt=\"Meereen.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/89/Meereen.png/20px-Meereen.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/89/Meereen.png/30px-Meereen.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/89/Meereen.png/40px-Meereen.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Galazza_Galare\" title=\"Galazza Galare\">Galazza Galare</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\"><img alt=\"Meereen.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/89/Meereen.png/20px-Meereen.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/89/Meereen.png/30px-Meereen.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/89/Meereen.png/40px-Meereen.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Skahaz_mo_Kandaq\" title=\"Skahaz mo Kandaq\">Skahaz mo Kandaq</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Hizdahr_zo_Loraq_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Galazza</b>: Oft have I heard that yours is the blood of <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon the Conqueror</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys the Wise</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron I Targaryen\">Daeron the Dragon</a>. The noble <a href=\"/index.php/Hizdahr_zo_Loraq\" title=\"Hizdahr zo Loraq\">Hizdahr</a> is of the blood of <a href=\"/index.php/Mazdhan_zo_Loraq\" title=\"Mazdhan zo Loraq\">Mazdhan the Magnificent</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Hazrak_zo_Loraq\" title=\"Hazrak zo Loraq\">Hazrak the Handsome</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Zharaq_zo_Loraq\" title=\"Zharaq zo Loraq\">Zharaq the Liberator</a>.<br />\n</p><p><b>Daenerys</b>: His forebears are as dead as mine. Will Hizdahr raise their shades to defend <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a> against <a href=\"/index.php/Second_siege_of_Meereen\" title=\"Second siege of Meereen\">its enemies</a>? I need a man with ships and swords. You offer me ancestors.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Galazza</b>: <a href=\"/index.php/Ghiscari\" title=\"Ghiscari\">We are an old people</a>. Ancestors are important to us. Wed Hizdahr zo Loraq and make a son with him, a son whose father is the <a href=\"/index.php/Harpies\" title=\"Harpies\">harpy</a>, whose mother is the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a>. In him the prophecies shall be fulfilled, and your enemies will melt away like snow.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Galazza_Galare\" title=\"Galazza Galare\">Galazza Galare</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Reznak</b>: Magnificence, you do not understand. The washing of the feet is hallowed by tradition. It signifies that you shall be <a href=\"/index.php/Hizdahr_zo_Loraq\" title=\"Hizdahr zo Loraq\">your husband's</a> handmaid. The <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wedding\">wedding</a> garb is fraught with meaning too. The bride is dressed in dark red veils above a <a href=\"/index.php/Tokar\" title=\"Tokar\">tokar</a> of white <a href=\"/index.php/Silk\" title=\"Silk\">silk</a>, fringed with baby <a href=\"/index.php/Pearl\" title=\"Pearl\">pearls</a>.<br />\n</p><p><b>Daenerys</b>: All those pearls will make me rattle when I walk.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Reznak</b>: The pearls symbolize fertility. The more pearls Your Worship wears, the more healthy children she will bear.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Reznak_mo_Reznak\" title=\"Reznak mo Reznak\">Reznak mo Reznak</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Hizdahr</b>: Words are wind, as you yourself have so oft said. No words of yours will secure this peace for <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Second_siege_of_Meereen\" title=\"Second siege of Meereen\">Your foes</a> require deeds. They would see us wed, and they would see me crowned as <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_Meereen\" title=\"King of Meereen\">king</a>, to rule beside you.<br />\n</p><p><b>Daenerys</b>: Marriage or carnage. A wedding or a war. Are those my choices?<br />\n</p>\n<b>Hizdahr</b>: I see only one choice, Your Radiance. Let us say our vows before the gods of <a href=\"/index.php/Ghis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ghis\">Ghis</a> and make a new Meereen together.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Hizdahr_zo_Loraq\" title=\"Hizdahr zo Loraq\">Hizdahr zo Loraq</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Hizdahr_zo_Loraq_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_11\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 11\">Chapter 11</a>, Daenerys II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_46\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 46\">Chapter 46</a>, Daenerys V.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot68.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot68.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thr